pageContext.description: Dimensions: L 109.5mm; Wbl 18.1mm; min W 9.7mm; W (at loops) 17.5mm; Wm 14.5mm; Bm 14.6mm; min.Blp 1.8 + 2.3; Ds 61.5 (?+),Typology: construction towards base of both lps; circ s. merges into loz. midrib with rounded crests; angular with blade wings rounded rather than sharp creases; s. with slight convexity close to m; which has a very thin top.,Manufacture: rounded low stumps of cg. gl. between blade base and loops, removed elsewhere, two perfns with ineq. shape in socket, have rounded edges - certainly cg. flaws: no defined bl. e. bevel,Condition: Mouth notch poss. damaged - hairline crack leads off from it - metal very thin here though and might be flaw; e. quite sharp - to some extent possibly due to flaking; some recent filing.,Attached Material: probably some material in socket end - wood?
pageContext.surface: Dull gold tex. surface (mini-craters) over much has flaked, especially at midrib and loops and edges, to smooth dark brown surface; gold flecked areas associated with filemarks.
